        The project comprises a senior loan for an amount of up to US$75 million to Turkiye Sinai Kalkinma Bankasi A.S (TSKB or the Bank), Turkey's first privately-owned development and investment bank.  Loan proceeds will be used to finance climate mitigation and adaptation projects including projects related to externalities of and investments in sustainable energy (energy efficiency, resource efficiency and renewable energy), green buildings, occupational health and safety, and  R&D investments in Turkey.

